{"type":"message","id":"5cddd93e","parentId":"8496c286","timestamp":"2026-03-30T12:15:31.022Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_X6xgbiAxZ3gIdyqpqnfkwP9B","toolName":"exec","content":[{"type":"text","text":"## Search: site:farside.co.uk OR site:bitbo.io OR site:sec.gov bitcoin ETF ethereum ETF inflow outflow SEC next 3 days\n**Engine**: tavily\n\n### Answer\n\nBased on the most recent data, the SEC has not yet made any announcements regarding the approval or denial of Bitcoin or Ethereum ETFs in the next three days. The latest filings from Volatility Shares Trust and Valkyrie ETF Trust II indicate ongoing preparations and submissions for their respective Bitcoin and Ethereum ETF proposals, but no definitive decisions have been disclosed as of today, 30/03/2026.\n\n---\n\n### Results (8)\n\n- **Bitcoin Long Term Holder Supply** (99%)\n  https://charts.bitbo.io/long-term-holder-supply/\n  Long-Term Holder Supply (LTH Supply) refers to the total Bitcoin supply held by entities that have held their coins for 155 days or more.\n\n- **BITX - SEC.gov** (98%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1884021/000138713123004119/btix-485apos_032323.htm\n  Volatility Shares Trust. (Exact name of registrant as specified in charter). 2000 PGA Blvd. Suite 4400. Palm Beach Gardens, Florida 33408.\n\n- **CoinShares Digital Asset ETF** (98%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1877493/000199937125000466/valkyrie-485apos_011725.htm\n  Valkyrie ETF Trust II. (Exact Name of Registrant as Specified in Charter). 320 Seven Springs Way Suite 250. Nashville, Tennessee 37027.\n\n- **Valkyrie Ethereum Strategy ETF** (97%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1877493/000138713123009893/valkyrie-485apos_081523.htm\n  Valkyrie ETF Trust II. (Exact Name of Registrant as Specified in Charter). 320 Seven Springs Way Suite 250. Nashville, Tennessee 37027.\n\n- **Volatility Shares Trust 485APOS** (97%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1884021/000138713123009033/ethu-485apos_072823.htm\n  Volatility Shares Trust. (Exact name of registrant as specified in charter). 2000 PGA Blvd. Suite 4440. Palm Beach Gardens, Florida 33408.\n\n- **Meeting with Representatives of Grayscale Investments, LLC and Davis Polk & Wardwell LLP** (96%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/files/ctf-memo-grayscale-davis-polk-042125.pdf\n  On April 21, 2025, Crypto Task Force Staff met with representatives from Grayscale Investments, LLC and Davis Polk & Wardwell LLP.\n\n- **[ ] this post-effective amendment designates a new effective date for a previously filed post ... - SEC.gov** (96%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1329377/000144554623008359/etf1_485a.htm\n  First Trust Exchange-Traded Fund. (Exact name of registrant as specified in charter). 120 East Liberty Drive, Suite 400. Wheaton, Illinois 60187.\n\n- **Tuttle Capital Bonk Income Blast ETF** (96%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1771146/000199937125013371/tuttle-485apos_091625.htm\n  ETF OPPORTUNITIES TRUST. (Exact Name of Registrant as Specified in Charter). Karen Shupe Commonwealth Fund Services, Inc. 8730 Stony Point Parkway,"}],"details":{"status":"completed","exitCode":0,"durationMs":8544,"aggregated":"## Search: site:farside.co.uk OR site:bitbo.io OR site:sec.gov bitcoin ETF ethereum ETF inflow outflow SEC next 3 days\n**Engine**: tavily\n\n### Answer\n\nBased on the most recent data, the SEC has not yet made any announcements regarding the approval or denial of Bitcoin or Ethereum ETFs in the next three days. The latest filings from Volatility Shares Trust and Valkyrie ETF Trust II indicate ongoing preparations and submissions for their respective Bitcoin and Ethereum ETF proposals, but no definitive decisions have been disclosed as of today, 30/03/2026.\n\n---\n\n### Results (8)\n\n- **Bitcoin Long Term Holder Supply** (99%)\n  https://charts.bitbo.io/long-term-holder-supply/\n  Long-Term Holder Supply (LTH Supply) refers to the total Bitcoin supply held by entities that have held their coins for 155 days or more.\n\n- **BITX - SEC.gov** (98%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1884021/000138713123004119/btix-485apos_032323.htm\n  Volatility Shares Trust. (Exact name of registrant as specified in charter). 2000 PGA Blvd. Suite 4400. Palm Beach Gardens, Florida 33408.\n\n- **CoinShares Digital Asset ETF** (98%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1877493/000199937125000466/valkyrie-485apos_011725.htm\n  Valkyrie ETF Trust II. (Exact Name of Registrant as Specified in Charter). 320 Seven Springs Way Suite 250. Nashville, Tennessee 37027.\n\n- **Valkyrie Ethereum Strategy ETF** (97%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1877493/000138713123009893/valkyrie-485apos_081523.htm\n  Valkyrie ETF Trust II. (Exact Name of Registrant as Specified in Charter). 320 Seven Springs Way Suite 250. Nashville, Tennessee 37027.\n\n- **Volatility Shares Trust 485APOS** (97%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1884021/000138713123009033/ethu-485apos_072823.htm\n  Volatility Shares Trust. (Exact name of registrant as specified in charter). 2000 PGA Blvd. Suite 4440. Palm Beach Gardens, Florida 33408.\n\n- **Meeting with Representatives of Grayscale Investments, LLC and Davis Polk & Wardwell LLP** (96%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/files/ctf-memo-grayscale-davis-polk-042125.pdf\n  On April 21, 2025, Crypto Task Force Staff met with representatives from Grayscale Investments, LLC and Davis Polk & Wardwell LLP.\n\n- **[ ] this post-effective amendment designates a new effective date for a previously filed post ... - SEC.gov** (96%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1329377/000144554623008359/etf1_485a.htm\n  First Trust Exchange-Traded Fund. (Exact name of registrant as specified in charter). 120 East Liberty Drive, Suite 400. Wheaton, Illinois 60187.\n\n- **Tuttle Capital Bonk Income Blast ETF** (96%)\n  https://www.sec.gov/Archives/edgar/data/1771146/000199937125013371/tuttle-485apos_091625.htm\n  ETF OPPORTUNITIES TRUST. (Exact